Kaas and Bruch.  Ice thickness = 15 inches.  No snow cover.  44 ft max reported depth.
Partly cloudy- level up 1"- approx. 2" rain late eve and early morn.
Clear- level dropping since last test
Extremely large Mayfly hatch the last 3 days- resulting in most areas of lake covered with larva skins.
Clear sky- mirror water surface.  Lake level: very high
Sunny- heavy rains this week- heavy flow of discolored water into lake from marsh
Lake appears to still be in bloom.
2 Loons present later that evening.  Great Blue Heron and Terns observed.  Willows in bloom.
Bright sun.  No clouds- no wind.
Blue sky with slight haze.  Lake has green hue although disk reflected white.
Sunny with haze and scattered clouds.  Strong wind out of southwest.
Blue sky with haze.  Light wind from west.
Blue sky with haze.  Slight wind from west.
Clear sky.  Very low water level.
Mostly sunny with cumulonimbus clouds.  Very low water level.
Slight wave ripple.  Winds North- North East.  Cumulonimbus clouds.
Slight wave ripple.  Water appears striated in sunlight with suspended particles.  Blue sky with haze- partly cloudy.  Blue heron flew overhead.
Sat. Path 23. Slight wave ripple.  Water appears striated in sunlight with suspended particles.  Blue sky with few cumulonimbus clouds and haze.  Water has green hue.
Dissolved Oxygen sampling did not work.
Sat. Path 23.  Slight wave ripple.  Bright sun with hazy sky.  Water color has green hue with suspended particles.
Slight wave ripple.  Westerly winds.  Cumulonimbus clouds.  Water has green hue.  White foam on shore.  Green heron flew overhead.
Sat. Path 23.  Slight wave ripple.  Clear blue sky with haze and cumulonimbus clouds.  South westerly winds.  Foam on shore. Floating weed portions present.
Sat. Path 23.  Winds from North.  Small waves.  Blue sky with slight haze.  Water has lime green hue with suspended particles.  3 Blue herons flew over reed stand.
Sat Path 23.  Slight wave ripple.  Winds from North East.  Blue sky with haze.  Water has green hue with floating particles.
Sat. Path 23.  Water has green hue.  Foam on North shore.
Sat. Path 23.  Moderate waves.  Windy- wind from North East.  Blue sky with few scattered clouds.  Water has green hue.  Foam on East/ South East shore.
Sat. Path 24.  Slight waves.  Winds from West/ South West.  Partly cloudy.  Foam on North shore.  Leaves are changing colors around shore.

Winds out of the south.  Sunny with sight haze.  Water has green hue.  Moderate waves.  3 hawks hunting overhead above east shore.  Reed stand at south east end of lake has no folliage visible due to high water.  Frogs and red-wing blackbird calls accompany the hawk's call.    Nate Rice assisted with the data collection.
Blue sky with cumulonimbus clouds.  Water has suspended particles but is very clear. Day of Satellite Path 23. Nate Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky with cumulonimbus clouds.  Water appears murkey with bands of supsended particles and algae bloom. Nate Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky with few cumulonimbus clouds.  Water appears murky with bands of algae bloom. Day for  Satellite Path 24.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.

Partly cloudy- wispy clouds with intermittent blue sky; slight ripple from North East; water color appears bright green with some floating particles in water column.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.

Sunny with sporadic cumulonimbus clouds; water level is very high - slow no wake is currently in effect due to high water levels; Blue heron landed in water to catch a fish close by as we collected the data; Nate Rice assisted with data collection.  Day of satellite path 23.

Overcast with overhead sun; waves from west wind.  Recent record setting rains seem to have contributed to filamentous algae increases at shore.  May be a result of addition of nutrients to watershed from runoff.  Water appears to have suspended particles in column at sampling site- as well as surfactant bubbles on surface.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.  Day of satellite path 23.
Bright blue sky with overhead sun; water appears to have green hue with suspended particles in rays of sunlight.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.

Steady west wind with waves- blue sky with cumulonimbus clouds- bright sun; water appears very green with striations and suspended particles.  North shore has clumps of brown colored floating algae.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.
Suspended particles in water- waves from west.  Counted 38 lake gulls in open water.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.
Water has suspended particles and is pea green in color with floating algae.  Water is cloudy and green mid-shore at north shore.  Steady waves out of west.   Nate Rice assisted with data collection.

Steady winds from west- slight waves.  Water is stirred up.  Spots of algae clumps on north shore.  Sunny with sporadic clouds overhead.  Lake gulls by bullrush.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.

Water is calm- striated and has bright green hue.  Appears as if algae bloom is present.  Sky is blue with slight haze.  Leaves are beginning to change around shore- warblers spotted on northern shore.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.

Bright blue sky with surrounding haze.  Suspended particles in water.  Loon spotted diving in open water accompanied by about 150 lake gulls.  Leaves changing around shore include maples- poplars and high bush cranberry.  Nate Rice assisted with data collection.
A loon pair is present.  Juvenile loon fishing in north shore shallows.  Blue sky with slight haze.  Lake appears very green.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
A few clouds; boat wake present.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Gusty wind from west and cresting waves.  Partly cloudy- cumulonimbus clouds- bright blue sky.  N. Rice assisted with data collection. Satellite day.
Slight wind from west with ripple.  Blue sky with sporadic clouds.  Lake gulls calling overhead.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.  Satellite day.
Wind from west.  Small waves and boat wake present.  Blue sky with sporadic clouds.  N. Rice assisted.  Satellite day.

Calm and bright blue sky.  Few clouds on horizon.  Algae bloom present.  Water has bright green hue and lime striations at surface.  Swallows chirping and swooping.  N. Rice assisted with data collection. Satellite day.

Algae bloom and decaying algae along north shore.  Boat wake present but winds calm.  Blue sky with haze.  One tree with crimson leaves at south shore.  Flock of ducks flew overhead.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Great Blue Heron circling overhead.  Sky is bright blue with haze in distance.  Slight wave ripple from SW.  Blue Flag Iris blooming on north shore.  Satellite day.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Partly sunny- bright blue sky with large puffy clouds.  23 White Pelicans riding thermals high above.  Satellite day.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Bright blue sky overhead; haze in distance.  Slight wind ripple from SW.  North shore Marsh Milkweed in bloom.  Juvenile loon fishing off southwest shore in morning- and on our voyage back to shore after monitoring- this young loon surfaced 5 feet off our bow.  Satellite day.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Bright blue sky with cumulus clouds.  Waves from NW.  Monarch butterfly accompanied our vessel to the deep hole.  Great Blue Heron fishing off shrub cover by Scout Camp peninsula.  Satellite day.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky with surrounding haze.  Slight wave ripple from NW.  Satellite day.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Spring peepers and chorus frogs singing from the east shore.  Buffleheads- ruddy ducks- scaups and mallards floating mid-lake.  2 wood ducks on north shore earlier in the am. Wind out of east-  redtail hawk circling overhead.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky- slight haze.  Slight ripple from southeast wind.  Great blue heron on eastern shore.  Redwing blackbird chorus in distance.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.  Satellite day.
N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Cotton candy-like clouds with intermittent blue sky and sun. Slight breeze from south.  New tree fall on point off southern shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Cicadas calling from shore.  Minnows schooling at surface- circling the boat.  Bright sun and blue sky.  Algae washed up along north shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.  Satellite day.
Blue sky.  Buffleheads in southeast corner.  Chorus frogs and chickadees singing.  2 hawks circling.  Calm conditions- slight breeze from northwest.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Blue sky.  Moon visible.  1 bufflehead still present this morning.  Green heron flew overhead on our way to monitoring.  Orioles on north shore.  Water level very low.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Blue sky with gray haze.  Calm conditions- water has green hue.  Helicopter dragonflies flying about on north shore.  Orioles still here.  Eastern Wood-Pewee call along east shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.  Satellite day.
Blue sky with white cloud puffs.  Light winds from north- northwest.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.  Satellite day.
Blue sky with large puffy clouds.  Visible algae accumulation on north shore.  Calm wind conditions with boat wake.  Cicadas calling from east shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky with high wispy clouds.  Hazy to the west.  Lake gulls present.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Blue sky with haze.  Monarch butterfly greeted us as we reached monitoring location.  Lake gulls present again.  Visible algae striations in water column.  Water level very low- trees surrounding lake appear stressed.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.  Satellite day.
Blue sky with slight haze- few clouds- 8 horned grebes present along with a larger group of buffleheads- scaups and ruddy ducks. N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Blue sky- slight haze.  Great blue heron flew over with fish in it's beak.  Red-tailed hawk circling.  Orioles singing. Slight ripple from SE.  No boats in motion. N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Blue sky- few clouds- wind from SW bringing small waves.  No boats in motion.  Mourning cloak butterfly greeted us on way out to monitoring.  Two days ago 40 white pelicans circled over lake and disappeared into the clouds heading SW.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Blue sky with cumulonimbus clouds.  Slight ripple from west.  Dragonflies busy guarding the north shore.  Asclepias incarnata- swamp milkweed- blooming on north shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky- algae bloom mid-lake.  Many lake gulls- about 200 arrived at 11:00 am.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky with patchy clouds.  Slight ripple from SW.  No boats in motion.  Cicadas calling on shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky- cool breeze- winds light and variable- slight ripple.   Kingfisher chattering on east shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky with intermittent clouds.  Waves from NW.  8 grebes fishing mid- lake earlier in day.  N. Rice assisted in data collection.

Partly cloudy- thin cloud deck mixed with blue sky.  Light wind from NNW.  Three Loons fishing in open water.  Baltimore Orioles just arrived. Buffleheads and Grebes still in town.  Great Blue Heron flew overhead squawking while Swallows swoop the lake for lunch.  Chorus frogs callling in NE wetlands.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Beautiful blue sky- slight haze on western horizon.  Buzzard overhead and swallows swooping.  Trees beginning to leaf out.  Lilacs in bloom.  Golden alexanders beginning to bloom on north shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Satellite day.  Breeze from SE.  Rose-breasted grosbeak pair with a noisy fledgling and Ruby-throated hummingbird with at least 1 nestling on north shore.  No boats in motion.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Satellite day.  Few clouds- light blue sky.  Light winds from S-SW.  Haze may be remaining from Canadian wildfires.   Boat wake present.  Marsh milkweed blooming on north shore.  Cicadas songs in background from east shore. 2 pelicans floated in SW corner of the lake last week.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Partly cloudy with bright blue sky.  Very calm- no boat wake.  Water has dark green hue.  Monarch visiting milkweed on north shore.  6 lake gulls present.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Satellite day. Blue sky with high clouds on horizon.  Algae bloom on north shore.  Baltimore Oriole seen in tree tops this morning.  Monarch butterfly visiting north shore Joe-pye-weed.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky with low- cumulonimbus clouds.  Calm winds.   Holiday boat traffic.  Algae bloom on north shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Blue sky with a few high stratus clouds.  Three-quarter moon visible over western kettle.  Many trees surrounding lake have already dropped their leaves.  4 Grebes mid-lake earlier.  Lake level so low that final Temp./D.O. reading for season taken at 38 feet.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

One common loon- a pair of red-breasted mergansers- a pair of mallards- and a few geese cruising the open water in the a.m.  Chorus frogs and spring peepers calling from wetlands to the north.  N. Rice assisted with data collection. One common loon- a pair of red-breasted mergansers- a pair of mallards- and a few geese were cruising the open water this morning.  Chorus frogs and spring peepers calling from wetlands to the north.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Great egret seen by west shore at kettle wetlands.  Five red-breasted mergansers- two buffleheads- gulls and Canada geese present.  Blue sky with a few clouds to the east. Slight ripple at lake surface from gentle north west breeze.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Pileated woodpecker seen on north shore this past weekend.  Oriole babies- goslings and duckings just a few of the fun spring sightings.  First swallowtail butterfly seen as well.  The lake is calm; heavy rains fell earlier in week.  Cottonwood blossoms dot lake surface.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Lake is aqua marine and sparkling.  As we anchored- great blue heron did low fly over- followed by the swoop of a barn swallow.  Call of northern bobwhite from shore. Marsh milkweed blooming on north shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Calm conditions- bright blue sky with a few clouds.  Gulls arrived this week- 20 present by west side of lake.  Algae bloom present- water has bright green hue.  Yesterday the following butterflies were seen on the north shore: 1 swallowtail- 2 monarchs- 1 red admiral and 1 purple admiral.  N. Rice assisted with data collection. (satellite day)

Satellite day.  Calm conditions- bright blue sky with a few clouds.  Gulls arrived this week- currently 20 present near west side kettle wetlands.  Algae bloom present. Yesterday- a number of butterflies visited north shore- including: a swallowtail- 2 monarchs- 1 red admiral.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Gentle breeze from west.  Flock of geese cruising north shore.  Hot weather weekend- algae present on north shore. Cicadas calling- and Orioles are back. N. Rice assisted with data collection.  (satellite day)

Blue sky with sunshine- haze on horizon.  Slight breeze from southwest.  Flock of terns on lake.  Great blue heron and sea plane fly over.  Grebes in mirror bay.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Blue sky- slight breeze with a few clouds.  Boat wake in area.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Satellite day.  Blue sky- a few wispy clouds.  Calm winds- boat wake in area.  Meadowsweet blooming on north shore. N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Satellite day.  Blue sky with a few clouds- calm conditions.  Lake water has bright green hue.  18 Sandhill cranes soaring and circling over south east corner of lakeshore.  Earlier this morning- Common yellowthroat call frequent by mirror bay.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Satellite day. Partly sunny sky- calm water.  Swallowtail butterfly flew over boat.  Barn swallows skimming lake surface.  Large school of iridescent small blue fish swimming past.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Satellite day.  Light winds from south- southwest.  High clouds- partly cloudy with some blue sky.  Rain earlier.  Cicadas calling from east shore.  Swallowtail butterfly flew past boat during lake monitoring.  Late summer Orioles visiting north shore this morning.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Satellite day.  Wind from southeast.  Monarch butterfly flew past boat while traveling to lake monitoring location.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Steady winds from southwest.  Two sandhill cranes flew over south shore of lake.  Two to three loons have been visiting the lake for the past week. N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Very calm wind conditions- partly sunny.  Horned grebe present in north shore shallow water. Pileated woodpecker call heard from south shore.  Eastern gray treefrog heard from east shore.  Eagle seen flying over west shore kettle wetlands later that day.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Wind from southeast- partly cloudy.  Spring wild flowers in bloom on north shore include wild geranium and golden alexander.  Treefrog call heard.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Satellite day. Blue sky with clouds.  Two herons on east shore. N. Rice assisted with data collection.

Water level very high.  Blue sky with slight haze and few distant clouds.  Lake surface has green hue and algae bloom appears present.  Song sparrow singing from south shore. N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Satellite day. Breeze from northwest.  Abundance of seagulls present.  Cicadas calling from east shore.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Satellite day.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Lake is very clear- beautiful aqua marine colors.  Bright blue sky- wind from southwest.  Loon- grebes and mergansers on lake in am.  Redwing blackbirds calling from shore.

Water appears dark green against white secchi quadrants.  Blue sky with puffy clouds- hot and humid weather.  Wavy conditions with southwest winds.  Yellow-rumped warbler song from east shore and dragonflies flying about during monitoring.

Water appears green against white secchi quadrants.  Blue sky- swallows swooping and singing- and blue heron flew over while monitoring.  Monarch spotted on north shore.  Recent weather has included rain and excessive heat.

QC Sampling.  Blue sky with haze.  Calm conditions. Secchi disk appears white against water with greenish hue. Water level is still high for this time of year- but dry weather has made the level decrease recently.  Damselflies onboard and monarch seen on north shore.  Blue heron calling in distance.

Calm water with slight ripple.  Secchi disk appears white against water with a dark green hue.  Clouds moving in during monitoring time.  Joe-pye weed on north shore a favorite for monarchs and swallowtails.  Goldfinches abundant on surrounding shores.  Gulls present mid-lake.
Light breeze from east- northeast.  Blue sky with cumulonimbus clouds.  Storms Monday and Tuesday evening damaged many trees around shoreline.
Secchi disk appears white against dark green water color.  Great blue heron flew over boat on way to sampling site.
Partly cloudy with blue sky.  Secchi disk appears bright white against dark green water color.
Yellow swallowtail arrived on north shore earlier today.
Slight breeze from southeast- partly cloudy with high clouds and blue sky. Oriole singing on north shore.
Satellite day. Breeze out of south- slight ripple and waves from boat wake.  Iris blooming on north shore. N. Rice assisted with data collection
Breeze out of southeast- slight ripple.  Bush honeysuckle blooming on north shore. N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Breeze out of northeast- boats in motion.  Partly cloudy.  Orioles on north shore. N. Rice assisted with data collection.
Satellite day.  Bright blue sky- slight breeze.  Boat traffic.  N. Rice assisted with data collection.
